prompt:
Produce a JSON object representing a product catalog. The catalog should contain an array of items. Each item must have an `item_id` (string), `item_name` (string), a nested `details` object (containing `category` (string), `price` (float), `in_stock` (boolean)), and an array of `tags` (strings).

{
  "catalog": [
    {
      "item_id": "string",
      "item_name": "string",
      "details": {
        "category": "string",
        "price": "float",
        "in_stock": "boolean"
      },
      "tags": ["string"]
    }
  ]
}

Include at least one example item.

runs:
```json
{
  "catalog": [
    {
      "item_id": "item1",
      "item_name": "Product A",
      "details": {
        "category": "Tech",
        "price": 50.0,
        "in_stock": true
      },
      "tags": ["Technology", "Software Development"]
    },
    {
      "item_id": "item2",
      "item_name": "Product B",
      "details": {
        "category": "Miscellaneous",
        "price": 20.0,
        "in_stock": false
      },
      "tags": ["Miscellaneous", "Gadgets", "Home Appliances"]
    }
  ]
}
``` 

